## 6. AnnouncementConsumer.java — complete

**File:** `D:/project/pt-gitlab/collabspace/collabspace-server/src/main/java/com/yottastudios/ns/collabspace/announcement/consumer/AnnouncementConsumer.java`

What it does when the delayed MQ message fires:
1. Parses `announcementId` from message body
2. Validates the announcement still exists, is not CANCELLED, is not a DRAFT
3. Sets status to `PUBLISHED`, saves to DB
4. Broadcasts to **all** connected WebSocket users:
   ```java
   WebSocketResponseModel webSocketResponseModel = WebSocketResponseModel.builder()
       .type(MessageTypeEnum.ADD_ANNOUNCEMENT.getType())
       .message("更新公告").status(200).data(null).build();
   String msg = JSONUtil.toJsonStr(webSocketResponseModel);
   webSocketHandler.sendAllUserToWebSocketClient(msg);
   ```
5. ACKs the message regardless of outcome (no retry)

Guard: `@ConditionalOnProperty(name = "mq.enabled", havingValue = "true", matchIfMissing = true)`

