## 7. Controller pattern — @ApiResource / @GetResource / @PostResource

**Files:**
- `D:/project/pt-gitlab/collabspace/collabspace-server/src/main/java/com/yottastudios/ns/collabspace/shared/component/scanner/annotation/ApiResource.java`
- `.../GetResource.java`
- `.../PostResource.java`

Standard controller class header:
```java
@Slf4j
@RestController
@Tag(name = "Your Tag Name")
@ApiResource(path = "/your/base/path")   // acts as @RequestMapping on the class
public class YourController { ... }
```

`@ApiResource` on the class = a class-level `@RequestMapping(method = POST)` alias.

Method-level annotations:
```java
// GET endpoint
@GetResource(path = "/endpoint", requiredPermission = false)
@Operation(summary = "Swagger description")
public ResponseData<SomeVo> myGet() { ... }

// POST endpoint
@PostResource(path = "/endpoint", requiredPermission = false)
@Operation(summary = "Swagger description")
public ResponseData<Void> myPost(@RequestBody @Valid SomeRo ro) { ... }
```

Both support: `requiredPermission`, `requiredLogin`, `requiredSpaceAdmin`, `externalOnly`, `tags`, `produces`.

